In 1991, it was granted the status of a so-called "pioneering investor" due to the Convention, as did the investors of a few other states.
The organization has the right to promote in the ClarionClipperton zone in the Pacific Ocean between Mexico, Hawai and Kiribati.
The area to be investigated by the investor is slightly larger than the former Czechoslovakia.
The seabed is divided there, it is a kind of Tatra on the seabed.
